<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,747,2033]" pageId="1" pageNumber="478">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,443,1863,1890]" pageId="1" pageNumber="478">Taxonomic affinities</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[460,651,1864,1890]" class="Insecta" family="Adelidae" genus="Nemophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="478" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alba">
<emphasis box="[460,651,1864,1890]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="478">Nemophora alba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
does not resemble any congeneric species in the details of forewing pattern. Nevertheless, light forewing colour and characteristic antennal brush suggest that this species might be related to the 
<emphasis box="[304,419,1936,1962]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="478">askoldella</emphasis>
species-group, as defined by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kozlov, M. V." box="[752,920,1935,1962]" pageId="1" pageNumber="478" pagination="459 - 472" refId="ref4235" refString="Kozlov, M. V. (1995) A taxonomic revision of the askoldella species-group of the genus Nemophora Hoffmannsegg (Lepidoptera, Adelidae). Entomologica Scandinavica, 26, 459 - 472. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 187631295 x 00116" type="journal article" year="1995">Kozlov (1995)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
